er RuPaul and singer k.d. lang in its first advertising campaigns. This lively chronicle reveals how M·A·C managed to not only defy the stigma associated with AIDS that alarmed many other corporations, but to engage in highly successful AIDS advocacy while maintaining its creative and fashionable authority.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAIDS (Disease)xSocial aspectszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 0aCorporationsxCharitable contributionszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 0aCosmetics industryxSocial aspectszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 0aFashionxSocial aspectszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 0aSocial responsibility of businesszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aHIV/AIDS.  aM·A·C Cosmetics.  aToronto.  aadvertising.  aadvocacy.  acause marketing.  acorporate social responsibility.  acosmetics.  adrag.  afashion.  agender.  aphilanthropy.  aqueer.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751093040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487510930423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487510930.jpg  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles